      'Git Bash': 'A bash emulation for Windows providing a Git command-line experience and Unix-style tools.',
      'PowerShell': 'The default shell on Windows Terminal — a cross-platform command-line shell and scripting language by Microsoft for system administration and automation, combining a command interpreter with a structured object pipeline. Navigation: ls / Get-ChildItem / dir (list contents), cd x / cd .. (change directory), mkdir x (new folder).',
