      'SQL Data Types': 'Specify the kind of data that can be stored in a column.',
      'INT': 'Stores integer (whole number) values.',
      'STRING': 'Stores text values; use single quotes in queries: \'x\'.',
      'DATE': 'Stores a calendar date value.',
      'VARCHAR': 'Stores variable-length strings up to a specified maximum, using only as much space as needed.',
      'TIMESTAMP': 'Stores date and time values. Use TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE (TIMESTAMPTZ) to represent a precise point in time regardless of the server time zone.',
      'DECIMAL': 'Stores exact numeric values with fixed precision and scale: DECIMAL(precision, scale), e.g. DECIMAL(10, 2) holds up to 10 digits with 2 after the decimal.',
      'Syntax': 'SQL syntax rules: statements end with ;, keywords are case-insensitive (convention: ALL CAPS), commands initiate actions, clauses provide instructions, operators perform operations (e.g. AS for aliasing, UNION / UNION ALL for combining result sets), constraints enforce data integrity, and NULL marks missing or unknown values.',
      'Connection': 'To connect locally in pgAdmin: right-click Server → Register → Server, name it, set host to 127.0.0.1. Open the Query Tool on your database to access a GUI for entering SQL commands.',
