      'Vite': 'A fast frontend build tool and development server leveraging native ES modules for near-instant startup.',
      'Webpack': 'A powerful, highly configurable static module bundler that builds a dependency graph of a project and combines assets into optimized bundles. Setup: install webpack, webpack-cli, babel-loader, @babel/core, and @babel/preset-env as dev dependencies; create webpack.config.js (specifying mode, entry, output, and babel-loader rules with tree-shaking via usedExports); create entry and module files; run npx webpack to produce dist/bundle.js; reference the bundle in index.html.',
      'Postman': 'A platform for building, testing, and documenting APIs through an intuitive graphical interface.',
